    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "dcc744b1_c47c36bc",
        "filename": "snapshot/win/system_snapshot_win_test.cc",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 79,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-06-12T16:54:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "When we need to #if on CPU, we always put x86 family first, and then other families.\n\nWhen we need to do something on a per-CPU basis that’s not implemented for future CPUs, we’d leave an #else #error.\n\nSo, here:\n\n#if defined(ARCH_CPU_X86_FAMILY)\n  // do x86 and x86-64 stuff\n#elif defined(ARCH_CPU_ARM64)\n  // do aarch64 stuff\n#else\n#error Port\n#endif\n\nNote that this matches exactly the #if cascade used in system_snapshot_win.cc.",
      "revId": "59c5c5465d115a8c093d5661f3792a1799bd7564",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
